name: 2,5-dibromo-p-xylene

Thus, two methyl groups are predicted to increase the melting point by around 2 x 23 = 46°C. Therefore, the total predicted increase due to bromine atoms would be 2 x 20 = 40°C. The sum of these factors provides the estimated melting point of the compound.
